1.name: Account
1.desc: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

3.name: AdvRefID
3.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

6.name: AvgPx
6.desc: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

7.name: BeginSeqNo
7.desc: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

8.name: BeginString
8.desc: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

9.name: BodyLength
9.desc: Message length, in bytes, is verified by counting the number of characters in the message following the BodyLength (9) field up to, and including, the delimiter immediately preceding the CheckSum (10) field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) For example, for message 8=FIX 4.4^9=5^35=0^10=10^, the BodyLength is 5 for 35=0^

10.name: CheckSum
10.desc: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "Checksum Calculation" of FIX Specification for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

11.name: ClOrdID
11.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID (49) or OnBehalfOfCompID (115) as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID (11) field.

12.name: Commission
12.desc: Commission. Note if CommType (13) is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

14.name: CumQty
14.desc: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled.

15.name: Currency
15.desc: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible.

16.name: EndSeqNo
16.desc: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo (7) = EndSeqNo (16) . If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo (16) = "0" (representing infinity).

17.name: ExecID
17.desc: Unique identifier of Execution Report (8) message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) for ExecType (150) =I (Order Status)).

18.name: ExecInst
18.desc: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

19.name: ExecRefID
19.desc: Reference identifier used with Trade Cancel and Trade Correct execution types.

21.name: HandlInst
21.desc: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

22.name: SecurityIDSource
22.desc: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID (48) value. Required if SecurityID (48) is specified.

23.name: IOIid
23.desc: Unique identifier of Indication of Interest (6) message.

26.name: IOIRefID
26.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types.

27.name: IOIQty
27.desc: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

28.name: IOITransType
28.desc: Identifies Indication of Interest (6) message transaction type

30.name: LastMkt
30.desc: Market of execution for last fill, or an indication of the market where an order was routed

32.name: LastQty
32.desc: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill.

33.name: LinesOfText
33.desc: Identifies number of lines of text body

35.name: MsgType
35.desc: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

37.name: OrderID
37.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID (37) field to assure uniqueness across days.

38.name: OrderQty
38.desc: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or par, face or nominal value for FI instruments.

41.name: OrigClOrdID
41.desc: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

42.name: OrigTime
42.desc: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

43.name: PossDupFlag
43.desc: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

44.name: Price
44.desc: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

48.name: SecurityID
48.desc: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource (22) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource (22) .

49.name: SenderCompID
49.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

50.name: SenderSubID
50.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

52.name: SendingTime
52.desc: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

55.name: Symbol
55.desc: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID (48) value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles).

56.name: TargetCompID
56.desc: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

57.name: TargetSubID
57.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

59.name: TimeInForce
59.desc: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders.

60.name: TransactTime
60.desc: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC - Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

62.name: ValidUntilTime
62.desc: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC - Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

63.name: SettlType
63.desc: Indicates order settlement period. If present, SettlDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlType (63) and SettlDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlType (63) is 0 (Regular).

64.name: SettlDate
64.desc: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format.

65.name: SymbolSfx
65.desc: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167) .

66.name: ListID
66.desc: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID (66) field to assure uniqueness across days.

67.name: ListSeqNo
67.desc: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo (67) of TotNoOrders (68) , 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

68.name: TotNoOrders
68.desc: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders (73) in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID (66) . Used to support fragmentation.

69.name: ListExecInst
69.desc: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

70.name: AllocID
70.desc: Unique identifier for Allocation Instruction (J) message.

72.name: RefAllocID
72.desc: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (71) = Replace or Cancel

73.name: NoOrders
73.desc: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

74.name: AvgPxPrecision
74.desc: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

75.name: TradeDate
75.desc: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

77.name: PositionEffect
77.desc: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

78.name: NoAllocs
78.desc: Number of repeating AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) entries.

80.name: AllocQty
80.desc: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account

81.name: ProcessCode
81.desc: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) / AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode (81) instance indicates regular trade.

82.name: NoRpts
82.desc: Total number of reports within series.

83.name: RptSeq
83.desc: Sequence number of message within report series.

84.name: CxlQty
84.desc: Total quantity canceled for this order.

85.name: NoDlvyInst
85.desc: Number of delivery instruction fields to in repeating group.

93.name: SignatureLength
93.desc: Number of bytes in signature field.

95.name: RawDataLength
95.desc: Number of bytes in raw data field.

96.name: RawData
96.desc: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

97.name: PossResend
97.desc: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

99.name: StopPx
99.desc: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

100.name: ExDestination
100.desc: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered.

102.name: CxlRejReason
102.desc: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

103.name: OrdRejReason
103.desc: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

104.name: IOIQualifier
104.desc: Code to qualify Indication of Interest (6) use.

106.name: Issuer
106.desc: Name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines, GNMA).

110.name: MinQty
110.desc: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed.

111.name: MaxFloor
111.desc: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time.

112.name: TestReqID
112.desc: Identifier included in Test Request (1) message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat (0)

113.name: ReportToExch
113.desc: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

114.name: LocateReqd
114.desc: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

115.name: OnBehalfOfCompID
115.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID (49) field and the firm originating the message in this field.

116.name: OnBehalfOfSubID
116.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

118.name: NetMoney
118.desc: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

119.name: SettlCurrAmt
119.desc: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

121.name: ForexReq
121.desc: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

122.name: OrigSendingTime
122.desc: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

123.name: GapFillFlag
123.desc: Indicates that the Sequence Reset (4) message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

124.name: NoExecs
124.desc: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

126.name: ExpireTime
126.desc: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC - Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

128.name: DeliverToCompID
128.desc: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

129.name: DeliverToSubID
129.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

130.name: IOINaturalFlag
130.desc: Indicates that Indication of Interest (6) is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

136.name: NoMiscFees
136.desc: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

141.name: ResetSeqNumFlag
141.desc: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

142.name: SenderLocationID
142.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

143.name: TargetLocationID
143.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

144.name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
144.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

145.name: DeliverToLocationID
145.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

146.name: NoRelatedSym
146.desc: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

147.name: Subject
147.desc: The subject of an Email (C) message

148.name: Headline
148.desc: The headline of a News (B) message

149.name: URLLink
149.desc: A URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) or URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator ). See " Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards " of FIX.

150.name: ExecType
150.desc: Describes the specific Execution Report (8) (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus (39) will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled)

151.name: LeavesQty
151.desc: Quantity open for further execution. If the OrdStatus (39) is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty (151) could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty (151) = OrderQty (38) - CumQty (14) .

152.name: CashOrderQty
152.desc: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as tradeable units (e.g. number of shares). The broker or fund manager (for CIV orders) would be responsible for converting and calculating a tradeable unit (e.g. share) quantity ( OrderQty (38) ) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

155.name: SettlCurrFxRate
155.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

156.name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
156.desc: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate (155) should be multiplied or divided.

157.name: NumDaysInterest
157.desc: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income. Note value may be negative.

158.name: AccruedInterestRate
158.desc: The amount the buyer compensates the seller for the portion of the next coupon interest payment the seller has earned but will not receive from the issuer because the issuer will send the next coupon payment to the buyer. Accrued Interest Rate is the annualized Accrued Interest amount divided by the purchase price of the bond.

159.name: AccruedInterestAmt
159.desc: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

160.name: SettlInstMode
160.desc: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions (T) message.

161.name: AllocText
161.desc: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount (79) .

164.name: EmailThreadID
164.desc: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

167.name: SecurityType
167.desc: Indicates type of security. See also the Product (460) and CFICode (461) fields. It is recommended that CFICode (461) be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments.

168.name: EffectiveTime
168.desc: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated), also known as "GMT")

169.name: StandInstDbType
169.desc: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

170.name: StandInstDbName
170.desc: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (169) (i.e. the Global Custodian's name).

171.name: StandInstDbID
171.desc: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

189.name: BidForwardPoints
189.desc: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

191.name: OfferForwardPoints
191.desc: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

192.name: OrderQty2
192.desc: OrderQty (38) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

193.name: SettDate2
193.desc: SettlDate (64) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

195.name: LastForwardPoints
195.desc: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate (194) . May be a negative value.

196.name: AllocLinkID
196.desc: Can be used to link two different Allocation Instruction (J) messages (each with unique AllocID (70) ) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

197.name: AllocLinkType
197.desc: Identifies the type of Allocation Instruction (J) linkage when AllocLinkID (196) is used.

198.name: SecondaryOrderID
198.desc: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID (37) used by an exchange or executing system.

199.name: NoIOIQualifiers
199.desc: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers.

200.name: MaturityMonthYear
200.desc: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate (541) field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options).

203.name: CoveredOrUncovered
203.desc: Used for derivative products, such as options

206.name: OptAttribute
206.desc: Can be used for SecurityType (167) =OPT to identify a particular security. Valid values vary by SecurityExchange: For Exchanges: DTB (Frankfurt), HKSE (Hong Kong), and SOFFEX (Zurich) 0-9 = single digit "version" number assigned by exchange following capital adjustments (0=current, 1=prior, 2=prior to 1, etc).

207.name: SecurityExchange
207.desc: Market used to help identify a security.

208.name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
208.desc: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

209.name: AllocHandlInst
209.desc: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation Instruction (J) message should handle/process the account details.

210.name: MaxShow
210.desc: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an Indication of Interest (6) ).

211.name: PegOffsetValue
211.desc: Amount (signed) added to the peg for a pegged order in the context of the PegOffsetType (836)

212.name: XmlDataLen
212.desc: Length of the XmlData (213) data block.

213.name: XmlData
213.desc: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See appropriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

214.name: SettlInstRefID
214.desc: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID (162) with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType (163) transaction types.

215.name: NoRoutingIDs
215.desc: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID (217) and RoutingType (216) values.

216.name: RoutingType
216.desc: Indicates the type of RoutingID (217) specified.

217.name: RoutingID
217.desc: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

218.name: Spread
218.desc: For Fixed Income. Either Swap Spread or Spread to Benchmark depending upon the order type.

220.name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
220.desc: Identifies currency used for benchmark curve.

222.name: BenchmarkCurvePoint
222.desc: Point on benchmark curve. Free form values: e.g. "1Y", "7Y", "INTERPOLATED".

223.name: CouponRate
223.desc: The rate of interest that, when multiplied by the principal, par value, or face value of a bond, provides the currency amount of the periodic interest payment. The coupon is always cited, along with maturity, in any quotation of a bond's price.

224.name: CouponPaymentDate
224.desc: Date interest is to be paid. Used in identifying Corporate Bond issues.

225.name: IssueDate
225.desc: The date on which a bond or stock offering is issued. It may or may not be the same as the effective date ("Dated Date") or the date on which interest begins to accrue ("Interest Accrual Date")

226.name: RepurchaseTerm
226.desc: Number of business days before repurchase of a repo.

227.name: RepurchaseRate
227.desc: Percent of par at which a Repo will be repaid. Represented as a percent, e.g. .9525 represents 95-1/4 percent of par.

228.name: Factor
228.desc: For Fixed Income: Amorization Factor for deriving Current face from Original face for ABS or MBS securities, note the fraction may be greater than, equal to or less than 1. In TIPS securities this is the Inflation index.

229.name: TradeOriginationDate
229.desc: Used with Fixed Income for Muncipal New Issue Market. Agreement in principal between counter-parties prior to actual trade date.

230.name: ExDate
230.desc: The date when a distribution of interest is deducted from a securities assets or set aside for payment to bondholders. On the ex-date, the securities price drops by the amount of the distribution (plus or minus any market activity).

231.name: ContractMultiplier
231.desc: Specifies the ratio or multiply factor to convert from "nominal" units (e.g. contracts) to total units (e.g. shares) (e.g. 1.0, 100, 1000, etc). Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc.

233.name: StipulationType
233.desc: For Fixed Income. Type of Stipulation or Prepayment Speeds.

234.name: StipulationValue
234.desc: For Fixed Income. Value of stipulation.

237.name: TotalTakedown
237.desc: The price at which the securities are distributed to the different members of an underwriting group for the primary market in Municipals, total gross underwriter's spread.

238.name: Concession
238.desc: Provides the reduction in price for the secondary market in Muncipals.

239.name: RepoCollateralSecurityType
239.desc: Identifies the collateral used in the transaction.

240.name: RedemptionDate
240.desc: Return of investor's principal in a security. Bond redemption can occur before maturity date.

241.name: UnderlyingCouponPaymentDate
241.desc: Underlying security's CouponPaymentDate. See CouponPaymentDate (224) field for description

242.name: UnderlyingIssueDate
242.desc: Underlying security's IssueDate. See IssueDate (225) field for description

243.name: UnderlyingRepoCollateralSecurityType
243.desc: Underlying security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description

244.name: UnderlyingRepurchaseTerm
244.desc: Underlying security's RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description

245.name: UnderlyingRepurchaseRate
245.desc: Underlying security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description

246.name: UnderlyingFactor
246.desc: Underlying security's Factor. See Factor (228) field for description

247.name: UnderlyingRedemptionDate
247.desc: Underlying security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description

248.name: LegCouponPaymentDate
248.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CouponPaymentDate. See CouponPaymentDate (224) field for description

249.name: LegIssueDate
249.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's IssueDate. See IssueDate (225) field for description

250.name: LegRepoCollateralSecurityType
250.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description

251.name: LegRepurchaseTerm
251.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description

252.name: LegRepurchaseRate
252.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description

253.name: LegFactor
253.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's Factor. See Factor (228) field for description

254.name: LegRedemptionDate
254.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description

255.name: CreditRating
255.desc: An evaluation of a company's ability to repay obligations or its likelihood of not defaulting. These evaluation are provided by Credit Rating Agencies, i.e. S&P, Moody's.

256.name: UnderlyingCreditRating
256.desc: Underlying security's CreditRating. See CreditRating (255) field for description

257.name: LegCreditRating
257.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg security's CreditRating. See CreditRating (255) field for description

258.name: TradedFlatSwitch
258.desc: Driver and part of trade in the event that the Security Master file was wrong at the point of entry

259.name: BasisFeatureDate
259.desc: BasisFeatureDate (259) allows requesting firms within fixed income the ability to request an alternative yield-to-worst, -maturity, -extended or other call. This flows through the confirm process.

262.name: MDReqID
262.desc: Unique identifier for Market Data Request (V)

264.name: MarketDepth
264.desc: Depth of market for Book Snapshot

265.name: MDUpdateType
265.desc: Specifies the type of Market Data update.

266.name: AggregatedBook
266.desc: Specifies whether or not book entries should be aggregated. Broker option if not specified.

268.name: NoMDEntries
268.desc: Number of entries in Market Data message.

270.name: MDEntryPx
270.desc: Price of the Market Data Entry.

271.name: MDEntrySize
271.desc: Quantity or volume represented by the Market Data Entry.

276.name: QuoteCondition
276.desc: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a quote.

277.name: TradeCondition
277.desc: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a trade

279.name: MDUpdateAction
279.desc: Type of Market Data update action.

281.name: MDReqRejReason
281.desc: Reason for the rejection of a Market Data Request (V) .

282.name: MDEntryOriginator
282.desc: Originator of a Market Data Entry

283.name: LocationID
283.desc: Identification of a Market Maker's location

284.name: DeskID
284.desc: Identification of a Market Maker's desk

286.name: OpenCloseSettlFlag
286.desc: Flag that identifies a market data entry.

287.name: SellerDays
287.desc: Specifies the number of days that may elapse before delivery of the security

290.name: MDEntryPositionNo
290.desc: Display position of a bid or offer, numbered from most competitive to least competitive, per market side, beginning with 1.

292.name: CorporateAction
292.desc: Identifies the type of Corporate Action.

295.name: NoQuoteEntries
295.desc: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet.

296.name: NoQuoteSets
296.desc: The number of sets of quotes in the message.

297.name: QuoteStatus
297.desc: Identifies the status of the quote acknowledgement.

298.name: QuoteCancelType
298.desc: Identifies the type of quote cancel.

299.name: QuoteEntryID
299.desc: Uniquely identifies the quote as part of a QuoteSet.

301.name: QuoteResponseLevel
301.desc: Level of Response requested from receiver of quote messages.

303.name: QuoteRequestType
303.desc: Indicates the type of Quote Request (R) being generated

304.name: TotNoQuoteEntries
304.desc: Total number of quotes for the QuoteSet across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoQuoteEntries (295) in each message that has repeating quotes that are part of the same QuoteSet.

305.name: UnderlyingSecurityIDSource
305.desc: Underlying security's SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

306.name: UnderlyingIssuer
306.desc: Underlying security's Issuer. See Issuer (106) field for description

307.name: UnderlyingSecurityDesc
307.desc: Underlying security's SecurityDesc. See SecurityDesc (107) field for description

308.name: UnderlyingSecurityExchange
308.desc: Underlying security's SecurityExchange (207) . Can be used to identify the underlying security.

309.name: UnderlyingSecurityID
309.desc: Underlying security's SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

311.name: UnderlyingSymbol
311.desc: Underlying security's Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

312.name: UnderlyingSymbolSfx
312.desc: Underlying security's SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

313.name: UnderlyingMaturityMonthYear
313.desc: Underlying security's MaturityMonthYear. Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the UnderlyingMaturityDate (542) field. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

316.name: UnderlyingStrikePrice
316.desc: Underlying security's StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

317.name: UnderlyingOptAttribute
317.desc: Underlying security's OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

318.name: UnderlyingCurrency
318.desc: Underlying security's Currency. See Currency (15) field for description

320.name: SecurityReqID
320.desc: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request (c) .

322.name: SecurityResponseID
322.desc: Unique ID of a Security Definition (d) message.

323.name: SecurityResponseType
323.desc: Type of Security Definition (d) message response.

324.name: SecurityStatusReqID
324.desc: Unique ID of a Security Status Request (e) message.

325.name: UnsolicitedIndicator
325.desc: Indicates whether or not message is being sent as a result of a subscription request or not.

326.name: SecurityTradingStatus
326.desc: Identifies the trading status applicable to the transaction.

327.name: HaltReason
327.desc: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading Halt.

328.name: InViewOfCommon
328.desc: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to Common Stock trading being halted.

329.name: DueToRelated
329.desc: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to the Related Security being halted.

332.name: HighPx
332.desc: Represents an indication of the high end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

333.name: LowPx
333.desc: Represents an indication of the low end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen

335.name: TradSesReqID
335.desc: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status (h) message.

337.name: ContraTrader
337.desc: Identifies the trader (e.g. "badge number") of the ContraBroker (375) .

341.name: TradSesStartTime
341.desc: Starting time of the trading session

342.name: TradSesOpenTime
342.desc: Time of the opening of the trading session

343.name: TradSesPreCloseTime
343.desc: Time of the pre-closed of the trading session

344.name: TradSesCloseTime
344.desc: Closing time of the trading session

345.name: TradSesEndTime
345.desc: End time of the trading session

346.name: NumberOfOrders
346.desc: Number of orders in the market.

347.name: MessageEncoding
347.desc: Type of message encoding (non-ASCII (non-English) characters) used in a message's "Encoded" fields.

348.name: EncodedIssuerLen
348.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedIssuer (349) field.

349.name: EncodedIssuer
349.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Issuer (106) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Issuer (106) field.

350.name: EncodedSecurityDescLen
350.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityDesc (351) field.

351.name: EncodedSecurityDesc
351.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityDesc (107) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityDesc (107) field.

352.name: EncodedListExecInstLen
352.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst (353) field.

353.name: EncodedListExecInst
353.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst (69) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst (69) field.

354.name: EncodedTextLen
354.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

355.name: EncodedText
355.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text (58) field.

356.name: EncodedSubjectLen
356.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject (357) field.

357.name: EncodedSubject
357.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject (147) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject (147) field.

358.name: EncodedHeadlineLen
358.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline (359) field.

359.name: EncodedHeadline
359.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline (148) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline (148) field.

360.name: EncodedAllocTextLen
360.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText (361) field.

361.name: EncodedAllocText
361.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText (161) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText (161) field.

362.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
362.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer (363) field.

363.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
363.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer (306) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer (306) field.

364.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
364.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc (365) field.

365.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
365.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field.

366.name: AllocPrice
366.desc: Executed price for an AllocAccount (79) entry used when using "executed price" vs. "average price" allocations (e.g. Japan).

367.name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
367.desc: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

369.name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
369.desc: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

371.name: RefTagID
371.desc: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

372.name: RefMsgType
372.desc: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

373.name: SessionRejectReason
373.desc: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject (3) message.

374.name: BidRequestTransType
374.desc: Identifies the Bid Request (k) message type.

375.name: ContraBroker
375.desc: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

376.name: ComplianceID
376.desc: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

377.name: SolicitedFlag
377.desc: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

378.name: ExecRestatementReason
378.desc: Code to identify reason for an Execution Report (8) message sent with ExecType (150) =Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

379.name: BusinessRejectRefID
379.desc: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

380.name: BusinessRejectReason
380.desc: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject (j) message.

381.name: GrossTradeAmt
381.desc: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty (14) * AvgPx (6) ) expressed in units of currency.

383.name: MaxMessageSize
383.desc: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

384.name: NoMsgTypes
384.desc: Number of MsgType (35) in repeating group.

385.name: MsgDirection
385.desc: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

386.name: NoTradingSessions
386.desc: Number of TradingSessionID (336) in repeating group.

388.name: DiscretionInst
388.desc: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffsetValue (389) is related to and should be mathematically added to.

389.name: DiscretionOffsetValue
389.desc: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst (388) , in the context of DiscretionOffsetType (842)

390.name: BidID
390.desc: Unique identifier for Bid Response (l) as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

391.name: ClientBidID
391.desc: Unique identifier for a Bid Request (k) as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

394.name: BidType
394.desc: Code to identify the type of Bid Request (k) .

399.name: BidDescriptorType
399.desc: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor (400) .

400.name: BidDescriptor
400.desc: BidDescriptor (400) value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorType (399) .

401.name: SideValueInd
401.desc: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

402.name: LiquidityPctLow
402.desc: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotNoRelatedSym (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

403.name: LiquidityPctHigh
403.desc: Upper liquidity indicator if TotNoRelatedSym (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

404.name: LiquidityValue
404.desc: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency (15)

405.name: EFPTrackingError
405.desc: Eg Used in EFP trades 12% (EFP - Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

407.name: OutsideIndexPct
407.desc: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

409.name: LiquidityIndType
409.desc: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

410.name: WtAverageLiquidity
410.desc: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

411.name: ExchangeForPhysical
411.desc: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

413.name: CrossPercent
413.desc: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency (15) . Represented as a percentage.

414.name: ProgRptReqs
414.desc: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

415.name: ProgPeriodInterval
415.desc: Time in minutes between each List Status (N) report sent by SellSide. Zero means don't send status.

416.name: IncTaxInd
416.desc: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

417.name: NumBidders
417.desc: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

418.name: BidTradeType
418.desc: Code to represent the type of trade.

419.name: BasisPxType
419.desc: Code to represent the basis price type.

420.name: NoBidComponents
420.desc: Indicates the number of list entries.

422.name: TotNoStrikes
422.desc: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66) . Used to support fragmentation.

423.name: PriceType
423.desc: Code to represent the price type.

424.name: DayOrderQty
424.desc: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all shares (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty (38) - ( CumQty (14) - DayCumQty (425) )

425.name: DayCumQty
425.desc: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

426.name: DayAvgPx
426.desc: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

427.name: GTBookingInst
427.desc: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

428.name: NoStrikes
428.desc: Number of list strike price entries.

429.name: ListStatusType
429.desc: Code to represent the status type.

430.name: NetGrossInd
430.desc: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

431.name: ListOrderStatus
431.desc: Code to represent the status of a list order.

432.name: ExpireDate
432.desc: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market's business practices

434.name: CxlRejResponseTo
434.desc: Identifies the type of request that a Order Cancel Reject (9) is in response to.

435.name: UnderlyingCouponRate
435.desc: Underlying security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

436.name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
436.desc: Underlying security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

438.name: ContraTradeTime
438.desc: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375) . (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

441.name: LiquidityNumSecurities
441.desc: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency (15) .

442.name: MultiLegReportingType
442.desc: Used to indicate what an Execution Report (8) represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securiteis, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

443.name: StrikeTime
443.desc: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

444.name: ListStatusText
444.desc: Free format text string related to List Status (N) .

445.name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
445.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

446.name: EncodedListStatusText
446.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText (444) field.

447.name: PartyIDSource
447.desc: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID (448) is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified.

448.name: PartyID
448.desc: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452) .

451.name: NetChgPrevDay
451.desc: Net change from previous day's closing price vs. last traded price.

452.name: PartyRole
452.desc: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified.

453.name: NoPartyIDs
453.desc: Number of PartyID (448) , PartyIDSource (447) , and PartyRole (452) entries

455.name: SecurityAltID
455.desc: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource (456) .

456.name: SecurityAltIDSource
456.desc: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID (455) is specified.

458.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
458.desc: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) .

459.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
459.desc: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) is specified.

460.name: Product
460.desc: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

461.name: CFICode
461.desc: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode (461) be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments.

464.name: TestMessageIndicator
464.desc: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

465.name: QuantityType
465.desc: Designates the type of quantities (e.g. OrderQty (38) ) specified. Used for MBS and TIPS Fixed Income security types.

466.name: BookingRefID
466.desc: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

467.name: IndividualAllocID
467.desc: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount (79) ).

468.name: RoundingDirection
468.desc: Specifies which direction to round For CIV - indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrderQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order.

469.name: RoundingModulus
469.desc: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required.

470.name: CountryOfIssue
470.desc: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

471.name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
471.desc: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

472.name: LocaleOfIssue
472.desc: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi

473.name: NoRegistDtls
473.desc: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions (o) message

474.name: MailingDtls
474.desc: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

475.name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
475.desc: The ISO 3166 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

476.name: PaymentRef
476.desc: "Settlement Payment Reference" - A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

477.name: DistribPaymentMethod
477.desc: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution.

478.name: CashDistribCurr
478.desc: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions - see " Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes ".

479.name: CommCurrency
479.desc: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see Appendix 6-A: "Valid Currency Codes" of FIX Specification.

480.name: CancellationRights
480.desc: For CIV - A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

481.name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
481.desc: A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

482.name: MailingInst
482.desc: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

483.name: TransBkdTime
483.desc: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

484.name: ExecPriceType
484.desc: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

485.name: ExecPriceAdjustment
485.desc: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

486.name: DateOfBirth
486.desc: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

487.name: TradeReportTransType
487.desc: Identifies Trade Capture Report (AE) message transaction type

488.name: CardHolderName
488.desc: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

489.name: CardNumber
489.desc: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

490.name: CardExpDate
490.desc: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

491.name: CardIssNum
491.desc: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

492.name: PaymentMethod
492.desc: A code identifying the Settlement payment method.

493.name: RegistAcctType
493.desc: For CIV - a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager's account types is required.

494.name: Designation
494.desc: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker's nominee or street name.

495.name: TaxAdvantageType
495.desc: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held.

496.name: RegistRejReasonText
496.desc: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instructions (o) has been rejected.

497.name: FundRenewWaiv
497.desc: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

498.name: CashDistribAgentName
498.desc: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

499.name: CashDistribAgentCode
499.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

500.name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
500.desc: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

501.name: CashDistribPayRef
501.desc: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

502.name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
502.desc: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

503.name: CardStartDate
503.desc: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

504.name: PaymentDate
504.desc: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

505.name: PaymentRemitterID
505.desc: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

506.name: RegistStatus
506.desc: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager

507.name: RegistRejReasonCode
507.desc: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions (o) has been rejected.

508.name: RegistRefID
508.desc: Reference identifier for the RegistID (513) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (514) transaction types.

509.name: RegistDtls
509.desc: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

510.name: NoDistribInsts
510.desc: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions (o) message

511.name: RegistEmail
511.desc: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

512.name: DistribPercentage
512.desc: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

513.name: RegistID
513.desc: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

515.name: ExecValuationPoint
515.desc: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

516.name: OrderPercent
516.desc: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor's total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor's cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

518.name: NoContAmts
518.desc: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report (8) message

520.name: ContAmtValue
520.desc: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519) .

521.name: ContAmtCurr
521.desc: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see " Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes ".

523.name: PartySubID
523.desc: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452) =Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole (452) =Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448) , PartyIDSource (447) , and PartyRole (452) .

524.name: NestedPartyID
524.desc: PartyID (448) value within a nested repeating group.

525.name: NestedPartyIDSource
525.desc: PartyIDSource (447) value within a nested repeating group.

526.name: SecondaryClOrdID
526.desc: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

527.name: SecondaryExecID
527.desc: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

528.name: OrderCapacity
528.desc: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order.

529.name: OrderRestrictions
529.desc: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

530.name: MassCancelRequestType
530.desc: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

531.name: MassCancelResponse
531.desc: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request (q)

532.name: MassCancelRejectReason
532.desc: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request (q) was rejected

533.name: TotalAffectedOrders
533.desc: Total number of orders affected by Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

534.name: NoAffectedOrders
534.desc: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

535.name: AffectedOrderID
535.desc: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

536.name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
536.desc: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order affected by a Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

538.name: NestedPartyRole
538.desc: PartyRole (452) value within a nested repeating group.

539.name: NoNestedPartyIDs
539.desc: Number of NestedPartyID (524) , NestedPartyIDSource (525) , and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

540.name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
540.desc: Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

542.name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
542.desc: Underlying security's maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

543.name: InstrRegistry
543.desc: The location at which records of ownership are maintained for this instrument, and at which ownership changes must be recorded.

544.name: CashMargin
544.desc: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

545.name: NestedPartySubID
545.desc: PartySubID (523) value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

546.name: Scope
546.desc: Defines the scope of a data element.

547.name: MDImplicitDelete
547.desc: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

548.name: CrossID
548.desc: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID (548) for Good Till Cancel (GTC) orders.

549.name: CrossType
549.desc: Type of cross being submitted to a market

550.name: CrossPrioritization
550.desc: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized.

551.name: OrigCrossID
551.desc: CrossID (548) of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Order Cancel Request (u) and Cross Order Cancel/Replace Request (t) .

552.name: NoSides
552.desc: Number of Side (54) repeating group instances.

555.name: NoLegs
555.desc: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

556.name: LegCurrency
556.desc: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

557.name: TotNoSecurityTypes
557.desc: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Types (w) messages are used to return results

558.name: NoSecurityTypes
558.desc: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

559.name: SecurityListRequestType
559.desc: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request (x)

560.name: SecurityRequestResult
560.desc: The results returned to a Security Type Request (v) message

561.name: RoundLot
561.desc: The trading lot size of a security

562.name: MinTradeVol
562.desc: The minimum trading volume for a security

563.name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
563.desc: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order.

564.name: LegPositionEffect
564.desc: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg

565.name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
565.desc: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg

566.name: LegPrice
566.desc: Price for leg of a multileg

567.name: TradSesStatusRejReason
567.desc: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request (g) was rejected.

570.name: PreviouslyReported
570.desc: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

571.name: TradeReportID
571.desc: Unique identifier of Trade Capture Report (AE)

572.name: TradeReportRefID

873.name: DatedDate
873.desc: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the IssueDate (225) and the InterestAccrualDate (874)

874.name: InterestAccrualDate
874.desc: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the IssueDate (225) and the DatedDate (873)

875.name: CPProgram
875.desc: The program under which a commercial paper is issued

876.name: CPRegType
876.desc: The registration type of a commercial paper issuance

877.name: UnderlyingCPProgram
877.desc: The program under which the underlying commercial paper is issued

878.name: UnderlyingCPRegType
878.desc: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

879.name: UnderlyingQty
879.desc: Unit amount of the underlying security (par, shares, currency, etc.)

880.name: TrdMatchID
880.desc: Identifier assigned to a trade by a matching system.

881.name: SecondaryTradeReportRefID
881.desc: Used to refer to a previous SecondaryTradeReportRefID (881) when amending the transaction (cancel, replace, release, or reversal).

882.name: UnderlyingDirtyPrice
882.desc: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket. "Dirty" means it includes accrued interest

883.name: UnderlyingEndPrice
883.desc: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

884.name: UnderlyingStartValue
884.desc: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the start of the agreement

885.name: UnderlyingCurrentValue
885.desc: Currency value currently attributed to this collateral

886.name: UnderlyingEndValue
886.desc: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the end of the agreement

890.name: MaturityNetMoney
890.desc: Net Money at maturity if Zero Coupon and maturity value is different from par value

891.name: MiscFeeBasis
891.desc: Defines the unit for a miscellaneous fee.

892.name: TotNoAllocs
892.desc: Total number of NoAlloc entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoAllocs (78) in each message that has repeating NoAlloc entries related to the same AllocID (70) or AllocReportID (755) . Used to support fragmentation.

893.name: LastFragment
893.desc: Indicates whether this message is the last in a sequence of messages for those messages that support fragmentation, such as Allocation Instruction (J) , Mass Quote (i) , Security List (y) , Derivative Security List (AA)

897.name: NoTrades
897.desc: Number of trades in repeating group.

898.name: MarginRatio
898.desc: The fraction of the cash consideration that must be collateralized, expressed as a percent. A MarginRatio (898) of 102% indicates that the value of the collateral (after deducting for "haircut") must exceed the cash consideration by 2%.

899.name: MarginExcess
899.desc: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

907.name: CollAsgnRefID
907.desc: Collateral Assignment (AY) Identifier to which a transaction refers

911.name: TotNumReports
911.desc: Total number or reports returned in response to a request

912.name: LastRptRequested
912.desc: Indicates whether this message is that last report message in response to a request, such as Order Mass Status Request (AF) .

913.name: AgreementDesc
913.desc: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction.

914.name: AgreementID
914.desc: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

915.name: AgreementDate
915.desc: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID (914) and AgreementDesc (913) was executed.

916.name: StartDate
916.desc: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral

917.name: EndDate
917.desc: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral

918.name: AgreementCurrency
918.desc: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

920.name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
920.desc: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

921.name: StartCash
921.desc: Starting dirty cash consideration of a financing deal, i.e. paid to the seller on the Start Date.

922.name: EndCash
922.desc: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

923.name: UserRequestID
923.desc: Unique identifier for a User Request (BE) .

924.name: UserRequestType
924.desc: Indicates the action required by a User Request (BE) message

926.name: UserStatus
926.desc: Indicates the status of a user

927.name: UserStatusText
927.desc: A text description associated with a user status.

928.name: StatusValue
928.desc: Indicates the status of a network connection

929.name: StatusText
929.desc: A text description associated with a network status.

930.name: RefCompID
930.desc: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

931.name: RefSubID
931.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific elements within a firm.

932.name: NetworkResponseID
932.desc: Unique identifier for a network response.

933.name: NetworkRequestID
933.desc: Unique identifier for a network resquest.

934.name: LastNetworkResponseID
934.desc: Identifier of the previous Network (Counterparty System) Status Response (BD) message sent to a counterparty, used to allow incremental updates.

935.name: NetworkRequestType
935.desc: Indicates the type and level of details required for a Network (Counterparty System) Status Request (BC) message

936.name: NoCompIDs
936.desc: Number of CompID entries in a repeating group.

937.name: NetworkStatusResponseType
937.desc: Indicates the type of Network (Counterparty System) Status Response (BD) message.

938.name: NoCollInquiryQualifier
938.desc: Number of CollInquiryQualifier entries in a repeating group.

940.name: AffirmStatus
940.desc: Identifies the status of the Confirmation Ack (AU) .

941.name: UnderlyingStrikeCurrency
941.desc: Currency in which the strike price of an underlying instrument is denominated

942.name: LegStrikeCurrency
942.desc: Currency in which the strike price of a instrument leg of a multileg instrument is denominated

943.name: TimeBracket
943.desc: A code that represents a time interval in which a fill or trade occurred.

944.name: CollAction
944.desc: Action proposed for an Underlying Instrument instance.

946.name: CollInquiryResult
946.desc: Result returned in response to Collateral Inquiry (BB)

947.name: StrikeCurrency
947.desc: Currency in which the StrikePrice (202) is denominated.

948.name: NoNested3PartyIDs
948.desc: Number of Nested3PartyID (949) , Nested3PartyIDSource (950) , and Nested3PartyRole (951) entries

949.name: Nested3PartyID
949.desc: PartyID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

950.name: Nested3PartyIDSource
950.desc: PartyIDSource value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

951.name: Nested3PartyRole
951.desc: PartyRole value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

953.name: Nested3PartySubID
953.desc: PartySubID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

954.name: Nested3PartySubIDType
954.desc: PartySubIDType value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

955.name: LegContractSettlMonth
955.desc: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

956.name: LegInterestAccrualDate
956.desc: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the IssueDate (225) and the DatedDate (873)
